results.name: Decimal expansion of eta_2, a constant related to the asymptotic density of certain sets of residues.
link: Carl Pomerance, Andrzej Schinzel, Multiplicative Properties of Sets of Residues, Moscow Journal of Combinatorics and Number Theory. 2011. Vol. 1. Iss. 1. pp. 52-66. See p. 62.
formula: Sum_{n>0} n P(2n+2) where P is the prime zeta P function.
mathematica: digits = 101; m0 = 2 digits; Clear[rd]; rd[m_] := rd[m] = RealDigits[eta2 = Sum[n PrimeZetaP[2n + 2], {n, 1, m}], 10, digits][[1]]; rd[m0]; rd[m = 2m0]; While[rd[m] != rd[m-m0], Print[m]; m = m+m0]; Print[N[eta2, digits] ]; rd[m]
results.author: _Jean-François Alcover_, Mar 17 2019
